AnnotationView - Class in com.mapquest.android.maps
AnnotationView
AnnotationView(MapView) - Constructor for class com.mapquest.android.maps.AnnotationView
Annotation View provides a View that is displayed on the map to show more information about a particular OverlayItem.

The annotation is displayed at a given GeoPoint (set by calling either #setGeoPoint() or providing an OverlayItem when calling AnnotationView.showAnnotationView(OverlayItem) that has an associated GeoPoint.

By default, the annotation will display a title and snippet as contained in the given OverlayItem, or a custome title and snippet can be set using AnnotationView.setTitle(String) and AnnotationView.setSnippet(String).

The annotation can be further customized by passing your own AnnotationView.innerView which will be displayed inside the annotation "bubble".
